case_address_found_1: Maricopa Rd.,3 Miles east of MC85
case_circumstances: This unidentified male who may be Native American or Hispanic was found deceased near a set of railroad tracks 3 miles east of MC 85 near the town of Gila Bend Arizona. The body was under a Palo Verde tree and was discovered by a Southern Pacific Railroad employee. The subject had brown eyes, brown hair, a mustache, and natural teeth. The body was clothed in a blue and white jacket, tan pants, white underwear, purple socks, and black shoes. He also had a below the knee amputation of the right leg and was wearing a makeshift prosthesis which consisted of a portion of a plastic bucket, string, a metal rod , numerous irregular pieces of rubber which were attached to the rod. The apparatus was then connected to a shoe. The stump of the leg was covered with numerous colored socks.
